Quad kiting isnt really all that fast.. Yes it is faster than normal exp in a good situation but the real pull of quading is you can just pick it up.. Normally people have to wait for groups. Manaburn costs 5 points in Class ability.. you have to atleast get mental clarity 3 and maybe want critical nukes 3 but thats optional.  5 compared to 27 isnt all that close but Rangers do have a lot more desirable class AA than wizards do in my opinion of course.. At 60 AA i feel im done.  <br>
<br>
Let's remember getting wizards into groups isnt exactly easy.  I have heard many stories of wizards who went LFG in a zone, got turned down and then minutes later the same members of the group came by and asked for a port.. That is how the class is preceived with with the flashy quad kiting and translocates. Just a taxi for whom to get your ports from.<br>
<br>
The general concensus from wizards.. Is they worked their asses off from level 1 to 60 (a great accomplishment more than a lot of classes) worked hard for that AA so they deserve manaburn.  Wizards are the hardest class to level to 50 period. Rangers are the easiest to level to 60 period.  Don't deny it cause I know its true I've played both.<br>
<br>
Since when did this become a class vs. class discussion anyway? its pointless.. each class has their ups and downs as intended. Stop trying to say one class is better than another to justify a manaburn change.<br>
<br>
I don't feel manaburn is overpowered. I feel some people abuse it and should be punished.. If you don't agree with me TOO BAD cause Verant doesn't care about any of us.. They do what they feel is best for the game no matter the amount of whining from all sides.<br>
