</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=saltamontes>Saltamontes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=Green>Moderator</font></span><br>  Posts: 405<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(8/13/02 8:30:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=417.topic&index=367>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Something I hoped never to see</span><hr size=1> To say enchanters are the most desirable class (&quot;raid or not&quot; I believe were the words used) is utterly ridiculous.  You can run a raid for 99% of the high end mobs in the game with a single chanter.  Anything beyond 3 or 4 enchanters is really overkill for most encounters in EQ.  You can run a raid with a single wizard as well, I don't deny that, however adding more and more wizards is actually a greater benefit to the raid than adding more and more chanters.  If you want to say most desirable grouping class then I'll give you that, I did levels 1-60 as a complete newb on my first char with zero PLing in under 50 days played, but please don't confuse that with raid desirability.<br>
<br>
As far as DC goes there isn't one luclin high end encounter I can think of that it's actually usable in.  Nothing DCable in the deep (not like I could get it across the bridge anyways), DCable things in Greig can't click through the portal with me, nothing worthwhile dcable in Ssrae (unless you count those little iksar slaves who die in an ae or two), DCable things in Seru can't port up with the arx key, and DCed mobs can't kill an old world dragon.  So DC chanterwise is only beneficial in one raiding zone in the entire game and that would be kael (or SS if you plan on running your pet way up to Yeli for the few minute long encounter and can do so avoiding everything on the way up).  <br>
<br>
MB on the other hand can be used for every single boss mob type encounter in the game and in some cases can actually be the only weapon used to kill these bosses.  So basically what I'm saying is comparing MB to DC is pretty silly as they're two totally different types of skills.<br>
<br>
And I am 95% sure that Tunare can be manaburned if you could actually find some poor saps to clear the plane for your attempt. =P<br>
<br>
Also if you're only doing 40-60 dps wtf are you doing on a raid?  Even if all you do is chain cast ice spear it's 1200/(3.5sec cast time + 13 second recast time) = 72.72 dps (not counting imp dmg 3 items or crits).  If you add in a sunstrike inbetween casts of ice spear you're doing (1200+1615)/16.5 seconds = 170dps (a cast of sunstrike will fit w/in the window it takes for ice spear to pop again and yes I know you can't chain cast that w/out having to use concussion here and there).  I'm not taking into consideration resists but I'm also not taking into consideration extra dmg from focus items or crits.  <br>
<br>
I don't claim to be this super smart wizard person but the math seems to speak for itself, wizards are by far the best dps against any luclin encounter hands down and if you say they aren't you're smoking something.<br>
